This paper deals with natural language understanding models and their robustness, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also involves machine learning techniques for improving model performance, which could fall under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural networks (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper uses a curated test set that involves visual reasoning, which could also fall under computer vision (cs.CV).
